00:11:30.450 --> 00:11:35.920
Why does the packet
change shape?

00:11:35.920 --> 00:11:39.690
The reason it changes shape
is because the group velocity

00:11:39.690 --> 00:11:42.960
is not the same for
all the frequencies.

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:47.550
The packet mostly moves with k0.

00:11:47.550 --> 00:11:51.690
And we haven't rated the
group velocity in k0.

00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:56.820
But if it would have
a definite velocity,

00:11:56.820 --> 00:11:59.130
we would have a
definite momentum.

00:11:59.130 --> 00:12:00.930
But that's not possible.

00:12:00.930 --> 00:12:04.260
These things have
uncertainty in momentum.

00:12:04.260 --> 00:12:10.180
And they have uncertainty in
k that we use it to write it.

00:12:10.180 --> 00:12:15.900
So different parts
of the wave can

00:12:15.900 --> 00:12:19.890
move with different velocities,
different group velocities.

00:12:19.890 --> 00:12:24.470
The group velocity
you evaluated at k0.

00:12:24.470 --> 00:12:28.440
But some part of the
packet is propagating

00:12:28.440 --> 00:12:34.380
with group velocities that are
near k0 but not exactly there.

00:12:34.380 --> 00:12:38.190
So you have a dispersion
in the velocity, which

00:12:38.190 --> 00:12:41.670
is an uncertainty
in the velocity

00:12:41.670 --> 00:12:43.750
or an uncertainty
in the momentum.

00:12:43.750 --> 00:12:47.680
Think, the momentum divided
by mass is velocity.

00:12:47.680 --> 00:12:52.510
So here it is, an
uncertainty in the velocity.

00:12:52.510 --> 00:12:55.095
And if you multiply
the uncertainty

00:12:55.095 --> 00:12:59.720
in the velocity times this
time that you can wait,

00:12:59.720 --> 00:13:04.280
then the change in
shape is not much

00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:08.060
if this product, which
is the difference of how

00:13:08.060 --> 00:13:12.080
one part moves with respect
to the other, the difference

00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:14.540
of relative term,
is still smaller

00:13:14.540 --> 00:13:17.690
than the uncertainty
that controls

00:13:17.690 --> 00:13:19.980
the shape of the packet.

00:13:19.980 --> 00:13:22.070
So the packet has a delta x.

00:13:28.060 --> 00:13:31.840
And as long as this part, the
left part of the packet, then

00:13:31.840 --> 00:13:36.880
the top of the packet, the
difference of velocities

00:13:36.880 --> 00:13:42.070
times the time, it just still
compared to delta x is small,

00:13:42.070 --> 00:13:44.770
then the thing
doesn't change much.

00:13:44.770 --> 00:13:51.490
So I think this is
