00:14:31.210 --> 00:14:38.940
How long does it
remain localized?

00:14:46.310 --> 00:14:49.250
So you have an electron.

00:14:49.250 --> 00:14:50.550
And you produce a packet.

00:14:50.550 --> 00:14:54.650
You localize it to
the size of an atom.

00:14:54.650 --> 00:14:58.160
How long can you wait
before this electron is just

00:14:58.160 --> 00:14:59.460
all over the room?

00:14:59.460 --> 00:15:05.300
Well, when we say this
t, and we say this time,

00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:08.600
we're basically saying that
it's roughly still there.

00:15:08.600 --> 00:15:11.810
Maybe it grew 20%, 30%.

00:15:11.810 --> 00:15:13.490
But what's the
rough time that you

00:15:13.490 --> 00:15:16.230
can expect that it stays there?

00:15:16.230 --> 00:15:20.720
So in this case, we can
use just this formula.

00:15:20.720 --> 00:15:28.820
And we say the time
could be approximately

00:15:28.820 --> 00:15:34.490
m over h bar delta x squared.

00:15:34.490 --> 00:15:35.990
It's fun to see the numbers.

00:15:39.500 --> 00:15:44.870
You would calculate it
with mc squared over h bar

00:15:44.870 --> 00:15:50.590
c times delta x over
c, this squared.

00:15:54.760 --> 00:16:01.485
The answer is about 10 to the
minus 16 seconds, not much.

00:16:07.140 --> 00:16:14.320
This is a practical issue
in accelerators as well.

00:16:14.320 --> 00:16:16.780
Particle physics
accelerators, they

00:16:16.780 --> 00:16:22.540
concern bunches, a little
bunch of protons in the LHC.

00:16:22.540 --> 00:16:26.530
It's a little cylinder in
which the wave functions

00:16:26.530 --> 00:16:31.190
of the protons are all
collimated very thin, short,

00:16:31.190 --> 00:16:33.880
a couple of centimeters short.

00:16:33.880 --> 00:16:40.420
And after going around many
times around the accelerator,

00:16:40.420 --> 00:16:44.440
they always have to be
compressed and kept back,

00:16:44.440 --> 00:16:45.850
sent back to shape.

00:16:45.850 --> 00:16:51.190
Because just of diffusion,
these things just propagate.

00:16:51.190 --> 00:16:56.430
And so it's a rather
important thing.

